==English==

===Etymology===
From {{m|en|add insult to injury}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# Harm, especially verbal, added to another, usually more substantive.
#: ''The cross-examination of the plaintiff was just '''insult to injury''', blaming the victim.''

===Phrase===
# The forecast called for more rain in the week, a fever and finals. To add insult to injury, she lost her glasses, and her backups made her look like a 16 year old learning how to drive. As she raised her hands with intention, she remembered the abundance of rewards that come with rain, despite its grey tinge to spring.